  "read": "This tests whether a single recompute tile can reuse QK/probability work for both dQ and dKV. The original combined line is key-major and atomically accumulates dQ; the newer query-major line keeps dQ local to the query row and atomically accumulates only dKV. The new query_sinks path keeps the same query-major schedule and emits d_sinks from already-computed row terms. The structured query-major variant computes the synthetic route inside the tile to isolate index-load overhead. The no_dkv and dkv_reduce_sink profile modes are diagnostic-only splits for dKV compute versus full atomic accumulation and do not produce correct dKV. This is still a diagnostic Triton prototype, and no LightningIndexer parameter gradients are emitted here.",
